Reasoning: The paper presents a data set extracted from a social sciences academic search engine, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The proposed description of user interactions could also be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of the data set for user modeling and search pattern recognition could fall under the category of social informatics (cs.SI).
